76561198003884833,Recommended,274520,34315456,Posted: 17 August,all,Fellron,"I don't ever write reviews but i had to give this one a go.I've played a lot of horror games and in general have pretty high standards when it comes to gaming. Honestly i did not expect much from a top down horror survival game, how scary could it be? Well not only is the game scary but it's also pretty damn good in a lot of aspects which i would like to elaborate on.Darkwood is a dark, grim, desperate and creepy world, it feels very inspired and it's easy to get emersed into.The atmosphere, sound design, characters, environment, tension are simply spot on.Your view is limited to a 90 degree angle infront of you while the rest is shadowy where only the environment will be visible... yet twisted and playing little tricks on you. The 90 degree angle is a big reason on why this game manages to give you that sense of dread like... oh i heard some rustling... is something behind me or is the game playing tricks on me?The sense of dread throughout the game is immense, especially at night, where you will be left at the mercy of darkness and the unknown.Nearly every location/landmark you uncover will have a story to it and gives you a chance to understand more on what happened in Darkwood and how people survive and cope with it.The combat system is surprisingly satisfying in both melee and ranged combat, but you will most likely need a little bit of time to get a hold of it.Enemies are diverse and have interesting strategies to deal with you. Some enemies go head on while others prefer to scare and mess with you.The user interface is clear and simple, you won't have much trouble figuring it out. The crafting system is also straightforward.I'm trying to come up with anything negative but it mostly comes down to length. Not that i wasn't satisfied with it but i wish it stuck around for a bit longer since it was doing so well.The game still offers a lot content for it's modest price tag so if you are a fan of horror games, you won't be disappointed picking this one up."
