,Recommended,274520,34320836,Posted: 17 August,all,Count Jackula,"TL;DR: Middle-Aged Snobby PC-Guy Loves This Game!I love this game, having bought it on its first official release day. I had been watching it for a while, but at the time I first spotted DARKWOOD I felt I owned WAY WAY WAY too many early release survival and/or horror games to snag another. Anyway, I am glad I found it, glad I watched it, glad it released, and glad I BOUGHT IT!!!! Toot Toot!This game proves that games can be HARD but can be FUN. EUREKA! This review is coming from a 39-year-old PC gamer who remembers when Atari 2600s were still in stores. (Man I thought those fake wood-grain panels were boss!)Anyway DARKWOOD: I never thought I would be so terrified or bug-eyed by watching a mostly-black PC monitor screen. At night in-game, I listen so hard my ears almost fall off! Wow this game can be tense at night, when all my character is doing is trying to impersonate a rock! Yes, a rock, preferably a heavy, black or shadow-colored rock.I love oddities and this game is a wyrd byrd. I love the strangeness. I love the warped perspectives. I love how hope isn't totally quashed, but the game yet remains overall atmospherically dreadful. The sense of humor is sly and downright Tolstoy-ish at times; Russian humor is almost indefinable, yet I know it when I experience it. If you liked the bizarre characters and lore of the Metro games or Stalker then you will enjoy this too, most likely. It has the same mood and sense of humor (just a totally different setting.)If you like survival, and building, and horror, and looting without having to get all grind-y, and atmosphere, and then a unique take on all of that, then try this game out. Even at the $15 price point, you will not be disappointed. I give it 7.9/10, maybe? It is a good game, and the price makes it approach greatness.EDIT: 2 weeks later and I am about 43 hours in, game about half beat, restarted several times, and really....7.9 was a bit conservative. I could go higher actually. DARKWOOD is just a really good game and I regret not supporting the early release. I am still floored that a top-down horror game has me this excited and immersed days after that first play and glowing review. I have a fast gaming rig that plays anything I want on ultra max settings; I have Witcher 3, the new DOOM, and plenty of other eye-candy to tear me away, but even with all of that? DARKWOOD is the game that gets all of my time right now. Darkwood FTW!"
