,Recommended,274520,34426987,Posted: 22 August,all,Kelso,"Let me start out by saying I absolutely adore this game. I haven't been able to put it down all day, and that ended up being 11 hours of playtime since I woke up...It does so many things well. It invokes a sense of dread and panic I have not felt from a game in a very long time, boasting some very strong Silent Hill vibes, both visually and narratively. The story is very minimalistic, begging you to find out what's going on in this messed up place. In a way, it reminds me a bit of both Dark Souls, in how you navigate the environment, lighting ovens (bonfires) along the way; and also of Five Nights at Freddy’s, where every single night is a nerve-wracking experience where you count down the minutes left until dawn.The top-down perspective also breaths some needed fresh air into the survival-horror genre, and the idea that only the things in your characters field of view are visible is a really nice touch. It leaves you feeling vulnerable, like someone is following you, hiding behind the nearest tree, and incredibly claustrophobic, especially in tight quarters.My only real complaint is that the combat can feel needlessly clunky, but I feel like that was the idea that the developers had in mind. Often times, it’s better to flee rather than fight, but it only gets harder the further in you get. Trust me on this: Chapter 2 is brutal.For now, I’m gonna need to grab some sleep and recover from this ordeal, but I very much look forward to continuing this mad venture soon.Oh, and did I mention that every new game is randomly generated? Guess I’m gonna be playing this through many more times, if I can even get through the first run..."
