,Recommended,274520,34340214,Posted: 18 August,all,gwalive,"First ever game review.I should preface by disclaiming that I've waited for the full release of this game for quite some time (being a huge survival horror fan), without ever playing it in its alpha or beta stages, so I can't comment much on its development.However, this game really is a welcome breath of fresh air in the stagnating horror genre. The game ackowledges the formulas of well-loved successful titles such as 'Sunless Sea' and 'Don't Starve' in its gameplay and lends an atomosphere and world akin to those the likes of 'Silent Hill' and cult titles like 'Pathologic'.They've emphasised the 'survival' element of the genre's namesake and this really hyperboles the tension and fear generated by the game. This contributes towards a relatively balanced game pace, although I'd recommend it primarily to those who prefer to play in short bursts, rather than hour long marathons.It explores some original concepts in its plot and setting (dark woods, if you didn't guess, though it's far more ineteresting than its title) and has some very interesting gameplay mechanics (i.e. crafting, night/day cycle).It's definitely worth the price tag for those who enjoy the survival/horror genres (either exclusively or combined) and I would encourage people to get involved as the community surrounding the game is very positive and active (at the time of writing) and the developers - from what I can tell - are responsive to fans of the game."
