76561198006301875,Recommended,274520,35401937,Posted: 1 October,all,The Watcher in The Dark,"This game has all kinds of the crap that I hate in games.  Never makes much sense, all the way through the end.  Clicking the wrong thing messes up the game forever, and you never get an idea what the wrong thing will be,  Combat controls are an absolute mess.So, with these problems, why do I rate this as one of the best, maybe THE best, horror games I've ever played?  Simply put, there is an elegance to the horror in this game.  It's not just that it is scary, though it is VERY scary.  But it is lushly scary.  The artwork, the soundscape, the pacing, the setup, it is all so well put together.  It's the game that I think horror gamemakers dream of making, and most of the time never come close.It's a triumph, despite its flaws.I'll never look at locking up my house at night the same way again."
76561198093350917,Recommended,274520,33713378,Posted: 21 July,all,Bloodrunsclear,"The atmosphere is already second to none!It's a cryptic and harsh game but because of this everything feels much more rewarding. In a way pretty difficult to find examples of in the 'survival' genre there are no food requirements. Meat is used as lures to chase away predators. Your focus can stay on looking deeper and deeper into the nightmare forest trying to find new people to talk to, trade with, or kill and new objects to combine or use to bolster your meager defenses. There's a vague map but it's enough to know your general location. Also the lack of voice over just makes the menace of the game more pronounced as you can't tell the emotion of a character talking and not even their state of mind, just their general location.I'm greatly loving this game and I'm glad it's gotten picked out of the doldrums it was languishing in. At full release I hope there's more of a prologue but that's been promised.Great music, great sound effects, meaty and strategic and suspenseful combat, lots of exploration. I've wanted a game like this for years and I hope this turns out to be it!"
