76561197977490548,Not Recommended,274520,34367193,Posted: 20 August,all,Enter the Wang,"After playing for a few days  I have to sadly give this one the thumbs down.The game is clearly unpolished after spending years in early access/development hell.The concept is great, but the game is failed by horrible quality of life issues, clunky controls and bad mechanics which all contribute to artificial difficulty.For instance the only way to dodge is backwards while most enemies have a charge attack which will just continue to slam into you. Sidestepping would have been a better dodge.Combat often involves madly running around in circles trying to avoid attacks while your enemies are unseen due to being outside of your cone of vision.Other problems include:-Mushrooms spawning directly under your feet even while you are in combat in your own hideout's kitchen.-Tech restrictions being clunky, nonsensical and a burden. You can build a pistol before you can build an axe, despite having an axe-head and wooden shaft from early in the game.-Barricading being poorly explained and implemented. Dogs can chew their way through a barricaded door and two wardrobes while you can do nothing to repair and/or reinforce them. If you go all out with barricading (which seems to be the only sane thing to do) you will also miss out on special events at night which can lead to items.-Monsters making a beeline towards you inside your hideout despite you not making any movement, them not having line of sight and sometimes you being in complete darkness. Why have atmospheric line of sight and stealth mechanics like being quiet and hiding to avoid attention if monsters just ignore these mechanics.-Monsters spawning DIRECTLY ON YOU while you are outside in the day time. I'm not talking a screen away, I'm talking you turn around and turn back and a huge dog is bearing down on you.-Many minor annoyances which all add to player frustration. For instance you have to relight ovens when returning to old hideouts, something you are only warned about immediately before monsters start spawning due to nightfall. RIP if like me you'd already barricaded yourself inside your generator room.I get that this is the developers first real game, but I don't think this is worth US$15.My advice is to get this for half price on a sale and blast through the main story on normal mode to minimise frustration, and only that if top down atmospheric horror games are your cup of tea."
