,Recommended,274520,34444010,Posted: 23 August,all,Poison,"So... what can I say?Before starting I should probably mention that I'm not the horror game kind of type. At all. I'm a little crybaby when it comes to that. Not playing the game itself, but coming even close to trying it out.This doesn't apply at all to open world survival games. I love those, and that's exactly why I thought I give this little game a try. Because it was standing out with its unique type of genre: Openworld, topdown, pixelated and obviously horror.What makes the game so special?To me this game is something unique, as already mentioned above these kind of genres normally don't mix well, but the developers of this game somehow managed to create a wonderful game, with a indescribable scary atmosphere. Not by using cheap jumpscares or realistic graphics (I'm looking at you outlast), but rather by using limited vision, horrific sounds and scary♥♥♥♥♥landscapes, with scary♥♥♥♥♥lightning effects.Coming to my next point: Exploration. This game is all about it, and sometimes you ask yourself wether you want to jump down that dark well, or if you want to go home and call it a day and maybe get enough courage to jump down the next day, which might reward you very well, but on the other hand can get you killed. Your choice.Now when it comes to nighttime, you better get yourself back home and barricade yourself in your hideout, but don't think you just go to sleep and let the nighttime pass, no. I remember my first few nights hiding in a corner and scaring myself to death whenever I heard steps outside, or even someone knocking on my door. Something happens EVERY night. And you should better prepared, because sooner or later something will get in and find you.Let's talk about the story for a second. I won't spoil you too much, but from what I've seen so far you can choose your own story and your choices matter and change the world around you. Something which I personally really like, because it's not linear (perfect for second or third walkthrough) and you have your own choices and ways to go.Limited ressources. This aspect might repel some people, but it is meant to force you to advance to new areas, and you get enough loot by exploring. The game is kind of random generated, meaning you' will find random crates and bodies placed on the map but pre-placed buildings and story-important stuff.There is also a skill- and craftingsystem to help you further decide your own things, like what am I to craft and what skills should I take over the others.Only thing which is kind of a drawback is that you can't go outside at night. You will die. No stealth, no harder enemies, no badass fighting, you will just die. Period.TLDR.: Atmospheric topdown horrorgame with a open storyline where your choice matters, skillsystem, and a crafting system. Only minor drawback is that you can't go out at nighttime, but I wouldn't try that anyways, at least not yet (At the time of this review I have only got 13 hours playtime)"
,Recommended,274520,11407635,"Posted: 25 July, 2014",all,Unamused Cat,"EARLY REVIEW (Subject to change)Update: 4/10/2015 build 4.1 AlphaThe game is coming along nicely. With each build come new improvements to everything across the board. By now it can be hard to tell that this is not a finished product! Please help fund it. Buy it now while it's ""finished"" but under construction and help a cult classic come into being.---I waited since this was announced on Greenlight, and boy was it ever worth the wait.First off, the ATMOSPHERE. It is amazing. I didn't think a top-down experience could really capture it so well, but it does because you can see the environment around you, sometimes eerily twitching or waving if you aren't looking at it directly. You can hear the wind, an occasional shriek, eerie ambience and the occasional crunch of a branch that might make you jump. Be careful, the noises you make can attract horrifying things, and the oppressive environment makes that delightfully clear the moment you see it. Who knows what might be hiding behind those wavy branches in the background?Next comes the exploration. Getting lost is VERY easy to do, so once again the location and feeling of real fear is stressed by this risk. You must make it back by dark or you will die, so be sure to know your pathway back, and hope to high hell there aren't any -things- to block your path on the way back. Look for materials for crafting, barricading, repairing or boiling mushrooms into a drug of sorts that gives you skills (A sort of leveling system). Craft a weapon immediately when you find what you need. But even with that, you're bound to want to run and hide from most threats.The characters that I have seen so far have also been extremely interesting. Well designed, excellent art illustrates them and unsettling dialog helps highlight what remains of the populace in this story.HOWEVER, there -are- bugs, as to be expected from an alpha, and the best way to play is just to expect the unexpected and report something if it blocks your progress, quit and reload. The dev team is very on top of everything and listens well to the playerbase. With the arrival of Alpha 2.0, it's clear they love their game and are serious about making things better for the players.Ending thoughts - Worth a buy if you like to support indie development and love a good, unique horror game, because there really isn't anything else like it out there, and you'd be supporting something great.NOT worth a buy when not on sale if you can't tolerate bugs and would rather have a finished product, but this one's going to be a hit. Grab it if it happens to be cheap at the time.This is something worth supporting. There aren't many indie teams out there with such passion for their product, and I believe it's already showing with each small patch.So far: 8/10, and only because of bugs and missing features."
,Recommended,274520,34543333,Posted: 27 August,all,Seanosilas,"I have never been so scared in my life.I can't even play more than twenty minutes at a time.The game features a randomized world in terms of resources and locations that aren't important to the story, for example; a shack that's near your hideout containing some fuel and mushrooms will not be there the next playthrough.That way each playthrough feels fresh in a way, but don't go into the game expecting a ""sand-box"".There are no jumpscares what so ever, the most scared I've ever been in this game, was on my second night, I was in the complete darkness, hiding in the corner of my room, with the door closed and a wardrobe against it, I could hear footsteps outside, then gradually the footsteps declined. I thought I was safe, then I heard a knocking at the door, one knock, two knock, three knock, then nothing.In the morning when light peered into the house, the wardrobe was no longer against the door and the door was half open, it took me a moment to realise that whatever had made the knocking noise, had gotten into the room but hadn't seen me.Survival aspects are decent, management of resources are constantly on your mind, there is no replenishing loot in the world, once you open up that crate and take the gasoline, nothing will ever spawn there again. No hunger or thirst, that's explained in the game.Be careful though, your character isn't some hero, fighting should always be your last option in this game, you MUST manage your resources or you simply will not survive, so this sometimes mean's sitting in the dark with no light's on to conserve that little bit of fuel that you plan on using to make a molotov cocktail."
