76561198122630095,Recommended,274520,35065519,Posted: 19 September,all,crossed,"Short version: Pretty epic game, play it :p---------------------I'm not great at writing reviews so I'll just throw a few thoughts about Darkwood in here.The sound design / ambiance is awesome, and combined with the twisted, often surrealistic imagery (especially when you get to see an object / NPC up close), they create a really dense, creepy atmosphere, which is the strongest point of the game (as probably pointed out by everyone and their grandma already :p )The game actually feels like a survival horror, most of the time it feels like you're barely surviving (on your first playthrough anyway), making through each day (and night) feels really satisfying.The figting while simple it's kinda skill based, every enemy is deadly, but you can take out any of them with whatever crappy weapon you can get your hands on, provided you're gud enough :pI haven't finished the game yet (28 hours in), but the story is great.. I guess...? :D I'm still trying to figure things out; the devs were admittedly inspired by Dark Souls, the narration is pretty vague, but it's all there if you pay attention to details, there are plenty of secrets to find  and mysteries to figure out for yourself. Anyway, it's interesting enough for me to just want to go on, play through one more day, find out a litte more.The game generally is very polished, everything works smoothly, haven't encountered any bugs yet.Two things that I personally don't like in the game:I really liked the thing that you can board up doors / windows and move furniture to baricade yourself, but pretty soon I realised they don't do all that much, it fells like a noob trap more than anything to waste resources and time on it.Normal mode is a little too forgiving, but on hard difficulty you have limited lives, and potencially facing a 'game over' screen 10-20+ hours into the game is not really the kind of challenge I like in games. There could be something in between.I might add some more thoughts once I finished the game...."
