,Recommended,274520,34359736,Posted: 19 August,all,Flock Mistress,"I was super hesitant going into the game regarding the idea of a top-down survival horror.But after 7 hours of game play, I am hooked. I very much enjoy the sense of urgency that arises when dusk arrives to make sure you are prepared to endure and survive the night. The artwork is great and fits the timbre of the game very well. I also enjoy the fact that the game pressures you to move further away from safehouses as resources are depleted in hopes of finding a cache or a new safehouse. The bartering system depends on your proficiency in surviving the night, or how well you manage resources to sell.The keybindings are intuitive and easy to learn, and engaging in combat is entirely optional. Although with high risk is high reward as enemies are typically guarding valuable items.There are no cheesey jump scares here which I adore. The game uses ambiance, glimpses of creatures in the distance (depending on your field of vision) and the knowledge of impending nightfall to make one soil their pantaloons.Huge thumbs up here.Fantastic game."
