76561197963728385,Recommended,274520,35455068,Posted: 3 October,all,Fen,"Surviver: 27 nights.Darkwood is survival-horror, par-excellence.  It reminds me most of games like Resident Evil 1-3, or more accurately, Silent Hill 1-3.  Add to this the fun of trying to secure your hideout each night and survive whatever unnamed horrors, or paranormal events, that come to visit. This game will leave you guessing.The gameplay cycle breaks down into 3 parts. Explore during the day and gather supplies to help you survive. Bolster your defences and refine your weapons to last the night. Finally, take your best loot, build high power weapons (because you've been making it through the night, right?) and unravel the main quests that let you progress to the next map.You might not think that a game with a fixed overhead camera can be that frightening, but between the sound design and the brutally limited view, I can honestly say it's been ages since I've felt that kind of panic playing a game.The game can feel incredibly unfair at times, especially when dealing with the full monster-type enemies. But dying only truely sets you back in time; there are enough resources to be found in the game that you can't truly screw yourself long-term.  The game is also brutal about not warning you when you're taking a fork in the story; don't assume there is only one way to advance. I tried to do a 'good' playthrough and during the epilogue I discovered I didn't even come close to doing it perfectly 'good'.  So on top of all that, the replayability is very high."
