76561198070722121,Not Recommended,274520,14306605,"Posted: 2 February, 2015",all,insanityscribe,"I'd been following Darkwood for about six months before it was released. It looked very fun, very scary, and really hard, but not hard enough to prevent you from having fun. Man, was I wrong.This game is obscenely difficult. Resources are scarce to the point that, if you run out of a particular item, you're basically ♥♥♥♥ed. Gasoline, arguably the most important resource in the game, is so low in number that its nearly impossible to divy it up between each gas-hungry tool that needs it.The ""scary"" part of the game, i.e. surviving the night, isn't scary. It's irritating. You are forced to sit in a dark room for four minutes, and if you move at all, you get wrecked by monsters with toothed-♥♥♥♥♥♥s for heads. If you don't move, nothing happens. It's either really boring or really stressful. Where's the fun in that?TL;DR: I REALLY wanted to like this game. I played it after every update to see what new additions had come with it. But it's just not fun. It never has been, and likely never will be. Spend your money on something worthwhile, like Undertale or Dungeon of the Endless."
