76561198071189687,Not Recommended,274520,11506718,"Posted: 1 August, 2014",all,Grandpa Phil,"I really want to enjoy this game, but I can't.It is very atmospheric and does a really good job making you feel creeped out.  The character designs are so bizarre and disturbing; they fit perfectly with what this game is trying to accomplish. The mysterious and fragmented storyline will make you immersed in the Darkwood world. Exploration is extremely exciting because you never know what you will find and the constant looming threat of The Thirst and the creatures of the night will always make you feel rushedWhere this game fails is the combat. Weapons are not easy to find and tend to break too quickly. You will more than likely be forced to craft your own weapons which will consistently deplete your resources, but you need these same resources to build barricades to protect yourself at night because fighting during night is near impossible. When you do manage to craft a weapon, good luck trying to use it. Your attacks have to be extremely accurate in order to hit anything. Here is how most combat situations will go for you: You aim your attack. The enemy jumps at you, attacks you, and jumps back in half a second. You swing your weapon and miss. The enemy jumps back in, attacks you, jumps back out before you can even aim your next attack. Before you know it, you are dead and could not even land a single hit with your useless weapon.This game seems to have so much potential, and I am excited to see where this game will go in the future, but the combat feels so broken, it isn't worth playing at the moment. I'm tired of being killed by the first enemy I encounter every time because the broken combat system doesn't give me any chance to protect myself."
