76561198092563412,Recommended,274520,11452952,"Posted: 28 July, 2014",all,Chillbacca,"The creepy atmosphere of this game will have the player looking in every direction.  Each sound or artsy detail comes together to create a surreal horror experience.  Although the game itself is not completely terrifying in the way that a game such as Outlast might be, it's difficult to deny this game won't cause your heart to beat slightly faster.  The game's intensity also adds a lot to the atmosphere and gameplay.  I constantly find myself running to blockade doors in the midst of terror and panic.  Another great aspect of this game is the fact that they are updating it.  For example, initially I had problems differentiating day and night; however, a somewhat recent update has brightened day and seemingly darkened the night.  Overall, I have thoroughly enjoyed my experience with this game.  Whether tension, horror, or retro-style RPG's are your thing, you will find something enjoyable about this game."
