,Recommended,274520,11445302,"Posted: 27 July, 2014",all,Darkovika,"Before I start, I want to say that this review was written during Alpha Build 1.1, and there are still quite a few bugs. The developers gently suggest against loading a save, and you get massive FPS drops when you get near areas- ESPECIALLY the Pig Shed, or whatever it's called.THAT SAID.I am SO glad that I bought this game. It is SO scary.You're probably thinking, ""How is a top-down game scary? You can just see everything.""No. No you can't.This game is top-down, yes, but all you can see is that hey, there's grass and not metal thingies. You can't see ANYTHING until your line of sight, much like the beam of a flashlight (NEVER EVER MISTAKE IT FOR THE BEAM OF A FLASHLIGHT, it is NOT a flashlight), alights on whatever is there. This includes mushrooms, traps, monsters, chests, and other forageable items. You will not know it is there unless your line of sight, flashlight, flare light, torch light, whatever is covering whatever it is you're looking for.The game is HORRIFICALLY frightening. You hear things way before you see them, and at night, you hear them and- hopefully, if your windows are boarded up and your back door blockaded- never see them. The prologue had me tense and on absolute edge, nearly driving me into insanity at the very end before dumping me into the actual game- and while the prologue is skippable, don't play until you've gone through the prologue. It REALLY sets the mood for the game and isn't a tutorial... Which is actually what I think it's supposed to count as.Tl;Dr: It doesn't show you diddly-squat despite being a top-down, the game is dark as BALLS and likes to throw monsters at you, and you never know what's coming at you until it's in your face. When I walk into a building, I walk into it with a weapon held high over my head and my pants soiled in terrified tension. I screamed when I walked into a chicken. A NORMAL, NON-MONSTER CHICKEN. It clucked and followed me, so I named it Kevin.Buy it. I highly recommend it. This game is good right now, which is why I was okay with buying it. I hope it gets even better down the line! Especially with that FPS drop thing."
