,Recommended,274520,14952385,"Posted: 18 March, 2015",all,SickTag,"A sickness plagues the land and a wood of mysteries to uncover...during your daylight adventures away from your house.  But at night, you drink from your well, and barricade yourself in as the darkness closes in, and creatures seek you out.The night was drawing in and the woods began to moan like a corpse.  I turned on the generator, and made my way into my house.  I dragged a stool into one room with two doors, one being the front door, and no windows, and dragged a lamp into the room with me.  As I did this, I could hear things beyond words moving around the outside of the house.  Foot steps?  What is that slithering sound like something running long fingers over the outside walls of the house?I set up a bear trap near the front door, where I think something might come from, when I hear something slither over the window sill and into the house, fromthe other room.  The sounds it makes are like a drowning man made of clay, and chills me to the bone.  I back away from the door to the other room, stool braced to keep it out.  It moves somewhere and the darkness thickens like a fog of ill intent.  I back into the corner behind the front door.The door rattles leading into the next room, and the nob turns slowly.  I raise my weapon and ready myself to fight and scream as madness in form that is walking in my house sets upon me.  But the door quiets.  I cannot hear it moving in the other room.  There is a slight crack in the wall I could peer through, but terror has me glued to the spot.  Is it lurking just outside the door, waiting for me to draw nearer so it can lunge against the foyer's door, swollowing me into the darkness in which it came?Silence.  Somewhere a dog howls, in the distance.  Perhaps it is the pack of hungry dogs that gave me chase the day before?  There is the sound of dogs fighting and yelping suddenly, and I near run to throw myself against the door to keep what is lurking out.  Nearly.I listen as the dogs fight somewhere in the darkness.  Did it leave and found the dogs instead?  Should I brace the door?  I am frantic and torn between what I should do.  I have forgotten the front door that I am hiding behind.  The lamp is pressed against it.Suddenly the front door bursts open, the lamp flies back, and the door, opening inwards blocks my view from whatever stormed in to eat me.  However, it blocks it's view of me.  I can hear it growling and thirting for my very soul.  It makes a grunt like the grave, and thuds foward towards the other door, intending to throw back the stool and search the house for me, room from room with the intent of eating me howling and thrashing.As it moves foward I hear the bear trap spring with ravenous metal hunger and the meaty snap as it slaps through monsterous flesh is sickening.  The thing unseen sreams a surprised and wet gurling scream and there is a thud.I slowly push the front door closed again and the thing's shape begins to come into focus.  It's hairy and a lump of clay like features, and the darkness outside thickens.  Suddenly the generator gives a dying cough and I am alone in the dark with the thing.  Is it really dead?  Where is it?  I can't see but one foot infront of me.  Does it have a friend near by?  The darkness caresses my cheak as I stand blinking into the dark.There is the sound of stirring outside.  I hear a door somewhere in the house creak open and then closed.  I grip my board with a couple nails hammered in it, a pathetic weapon for defense, and it gives me no comfort.  There is a sound again outside, but it is just outside the front door.  It sounds like...sniffing...smelling me in the dark...The darkness begins to receed, but whatever is outside is moving again, and I can hear it at one of the windows in the room next to mine, the one with only a door and a stool keeping me safe.  It moves off into another room and then there is silence.The rays of the sun peek over the horizon and I know that I have made it through the night.  But will I survive another, or another after that?  How long will my luck hold out and will I find enough supplies to fortify my home?  The thing that died is gone, except for a wet splat where it was.  I step outside and check the outisde of the house and see a couple windows that I barricaded are open to the elements.  I move off to the north towards the sounds of the dogs from the night.  Just over the next clearing are number of blood puddles.  This is all that remains of the dogs.  Something came out of the woods and dragged them dying and yelping into the woods.  This pack of dogs could have easily killed me the day before, and something easily came for them this past night.  What do I do if it comes for me tonight?"
