76561198028170373,Recommended,274520,20309827,"Posted: 4 January, 2016",all,Benzin,"Update July 2017Yay! game is about to release! cant wait to play the (finally!) finished version!Update Dec. 2016:Looks like the devs are back and hard at work on this title again. And since my original toughts on the game still stand (it IS a good game), i think its fair that i change the review back to positive.Hope to see the whole & finished game soon!Update Sep. 2016:Im changing my review to negative because it is now obvious the devs are ""too busy"" to finish this game. Months go by without any updates.Yes, i know its an indie game, and the devs are a small team. But still its just too much time without any updates. Other EA games i bought at about the same time as darkwood (namely Subterrain and Frozen state) are now OUT of early accesss, and this game hasnt even been updated! This one was ""released"" in Jul, 2014 For christ sake! earlier than Frozen state or subterrain!Too bad really, i like the game and i think it had potential.This game is still in early access, and imho its allready way better than many (dare i say most?) ""finished"", sometimes expensive survival horror games out there today.Its also very polished, and by far the most bug free and functional pre-release game ibe seen. The only reason you know its an unfinished/early access game is because it sais so on the main menu. If they removed this legend you really wouldnt notice, as i have yet to find a serious bug or problem with the game.It has great atmosphere, great immersion, smart & simple crafting mechanics, ZERO handholding (key for a survival game), no ""objective markers"", ""magic GPS like"" positioning on the map (you actually need to keep track of where you are or youll get lost & die!), This game actually makes you feel ""uneasy"" (or just plain scared if you scare easy) during the nights, when you are standing in the corner of your room, behind your barricades & traps, praying that they manage to keep the evil creatures outside.Another thing i like is that besides being a survival game it has a story. I have not finished the game yet, but so far i like the story.Basically (setting the story aside) the gameplay is you need to explore the map to find resoruces (gas, wood, metal parts, building materials, etc) to secure your house for the night, and you must do this during the day, as going out at night is suicide. Then setup your defences and survive the night, the time when ghosts, monsters and evil creatures (no zombies this time THANK GOD!), will try to get inside your house and kill you.Do you turn the generator on for some light in the night (at the expense of gas)? or do you set traps, barricades and stay perfectly still on a corner IN COMPLETE DARKNESS without making noise, hoping they wont notice you? Either way you need to remember you are not some kung-fu expert, RPG welding rambo who can kill anything, and the best way to survive is to avoid combat as much as possible, so if you want a combat game, this is NOT it. This one is about smarts, survival, planning and managing your time wisely.I almost forgot, if you think that because this game is ""top down view"" youre gonna be able to exploit this to your advantage (like see whats behind you), youre in for an un-pleasant surprise. You have a vision ""cone"", and tough you can see the map arround you, can only see whats in front of you. Just like you would in a First person game.If you like survival horror games, you will most likely love this one. Be warned thoug, its game is HARD. like i said there is no handholding, no ""radar"" or ""minimap"" and one wrong call might me your last.10/10 totally recommended!"
76561198086102485,Recommended,274520,33858625,Posted: 28 July,all,Winchester,"If I could describe this game's gameplay with one word, it would be dreadful. Not because I hate the way it plays, I actually love it, but because even from tge starting prologue, you know you're not playing as some invincible action hero, you're just playing as someone who's trying to survive in incredibly harsh conditions.......Like the description says, you're scavaging and fighting during the day, but as soon as dusk sets, you'll find yourself sprinting back to your hideout, because this game has the scariest night system I have personally experienced. You can hear the creatures walking outside looking for a way in, you can hear the cracking of wood as they try, and eventually break your barricades, you can hear their heavy footsteps as they look for a way to get to you. The game is very unforgiving because you never get to feel like a hero, I found myself cowering in fear as I uselessly used wardroves to try and cover the door at night, to keep me away from them, and literally pushing the wardrove back as they pushed it toward the room, and eventually got in.The soundtrack is incredibly fitting and the game OOZES with atmosphere, the music that plays when you're just mere minutes away from the safety of daylight is so perfect for the situation, because you simply made it through ONE night, and managed to escape death one more time, and you gotta do it all again the next day. I really recommend this game to everyone who enjoys a survival horror experience. I know I know it's a topdown thirdperson game but it makes up for this by only showing what's inside your character's field of view, you cannot see behind you, all you see is black and white.I think if anybody likes an alternate survival experience, and a real take on horror, they should spend 15$ wisely on this game, you surely won't regret it!"
