76561198006573708,Recommended,274520,34353916,Posted: 19 August,all,cradoi10,"The atmosphere is fantastic, the game can be hard with 3 different settings (inf lives, 3 lives, permadeath).I ended up buying it not just because it's intelligent, no-jump-scares survival horror, with great crafting elemnts, and an almost Geiger-esque atmosphere, but because the gameplay is solid.Haven't felt this tense since Dead Space 1.Highly reccomended for more mature horror gamers, who expect more than shallow scares.-------------------------TWO CAVEATS: First, I am concerned about the length, as I've read conflicting reports. On permadeath however, I haven't made it past day 2 yet, which is solid as far as gameplay time.Second, the areas and maps in the game are only quasi-random. Loot drops, and map shape are different every time, but you'll see the same set pieces in random locations. This informs the first caveat, as I can't tell how large the maps are. Definitely does not seem like a sandbox game, it tells a linear story, in a Ullyses-like way.To the developers' huge credit, this is apparent before you purchase, in several forums. At no point was this ever presented as a game where you farm loot and experience, which is an honest thing to say on their part. Very impressed."
