76561198072846249,Recommended,274520,34452102,Posted: 23 August,all,manusveritas,"I've only played a few hours, but I'm engrossed. Even though it is a top down 2d game, it is incredibly engaging and honestly unsettling. It's part mystery and investigation, part survival and resource management. The mood that it creates with its disturbing art style and well composed music is foreboding and ominous, and it does a fantastic job of heightening the tension throughout your gameplay.The game does not coddle you at all, and it really harkens back to a different era of gaming. Combat is difficult and unforgiving, even on the default settings. The game takes you through a day/night cycle, exploring in the light and taking shelter in your hideout in the dark. You must pay close attention to noises and movement, anything could quite easily kill you if you aren't alert, and you can't see anything that isn't in front of your character. The entire combat and exploration style goes a long way to preserving that feeling of apprehension and fear, and I've already become accustomed to freezing and looking around whenever I hear an unexpected noise. It has truly been a delightful and challenging experience.Even with just a handful of hours played, I can't recommend this game enough, it is well worth its modest price tag. Seriously, you should definitely buy it."
