,Recommended,274520,34838345,Posted: 9 September,all,Wafflecopter,"Video review with more depth:https://youtu.be/kkLquJcFyEAPROS:-Incredibly well-done horror aspect-All enemies can kill you easily-Safe houses aren't necessarily safe-Random supernatural events during the night make you question your own sanity-Dynamic music provides an atmosphere of dread and tension-While some weapons can OHK enemies, they're usually expensive and can be lost forever-High difficulty curve adds to the horror aspect-Very little hand-holding; you learn most of the game through trial and error-Weapons take practice to use properly-Resources do not respawn in the game world - once you take them, they're gone-Survival part isn't as good as the horror aspect, but still great nonetheless-Most of your time is spent searching the forest for supplies just to survive the night-Supplies are extremely valuable and are often crucial to your survival-Mysterious and well-developed game world-Game's backstory is intentionally kept vague to add a sense of mystery-Destroyed tanks, burned houses, and absorbed corpses give off a sense of despair-Interesting and unique characters, such as the wolfman and the trader-The setting of the game itself seems like the enemy here-Lots of gameplay to be had, since completing missions takes a lot of preparation-Vision is done very well for a top-down game - 90 degree cone shows enemies and items-Beautiful animation for a 2D game-Overall art style is very nice, showing forest and fields in black, white and colorNEUTRALS-The game is very slow, typical for most survival gamesCONS-AI sometimes glitches out, tries to run through walls-Lots of aliasing in-game and in the menusThis could be one of the best games of this decade, up there with Limbo and Metro in terms of atmosphere. Also it's only 15 dollars. However, if you don't like survival games, then I'd stay away.Score: 10/10 (Perfect)"
