,Recommended,274520,34999302,Posted: 16 September,all,Teuton,"Had Darkwood on my radar for a while. It's hard to tell what this game actually is just from Youtube videos so I made use of the free download offered by the devs. After six ingame days I was fully convinced and bought it. I would call it a mix of Hotline Miami and Diablo 2, with a heavy dose of Lovecraft. For each ""act"" there's a base and you explore the locations and quests around that base. Combat is slow and dangerous and often it's better to avoid fights, although there are some creatures worth looting. The night invasions are too hard for me, not gonna lie. I wouldn't make it past Act2 without the ""normal"" difficulty. My favorite part so far has been ""The Village"" with the chickens and pigs... one of the most creepy/unsettling locations in horror games ever. The sound design in Darkwood is excellent. Definitely got my money's worth."
