76561198153181676,Recommended,274520,35076766,Posted: 19 September,all,Revenant_Soul,"Awesome game lots of good elements so far!!! So I'm about an hour or two in after getting controller set up and used to controls in the games prologue.Reasons to get:+ Story implementation-I have experienced the beginning of what seems to be a interesting story line, there is some journal reading and short in game cut scenes that don't really break emersion that i hope continues.+ Base defense elements- Not to spoil but there is barricading and trap placement involved as you find out very early on+No hand holding- to be fair their is a little bit of a learning curve (at least on hard mode Idk about normal yet) the game tells you just enough you have to figure out what to do and the consequences of how you spend your time on your own which is challenging but rewarding after you figure it out (huge helpful hint: there are days and nights to the game so be careful)+ Wonderful and situationally appropriate suspenseful music- considering the art style, psychological horror vibes, and top down view point the music fits exceptionally well and adds to the game in a way that expresses the feeling of worry and adds unseen detail even when only able to view in 3rd person. that being said i feel the intentional obscurity is welcome as that is something i love in some of my favorite horror games+day night cycles+crafting traps, weapons, items, medical supplies, etc.+obtainable skills+NPC interaction and choices with consequences(all for a $15 price point guys)I praise the subtle elements like intelligible sounds at creepy moments and doors opening with nothing there, and also the light/dark field of view thats surprised me already a couple of times as you never know whats making that sound or lying in wait until you shine some light. The vague map is cool too. It shows critical points but doesn't hold your hand.My only current wish is for more interaction with obtainable objects like flavor script for checking environment and interacting/checking inventory objects. Understandably not a necessary feature but a welcome one for the depth it adds to emersion and detail for those like me that those optional things interest."
