76561198118846879,Not Recommended,274520,34683122,Posted: 2 September,all,lieblingslied,"Such an awesome game. It's a lot of fun and at the same time exciting and creepy. I can definitely recommend  it :)edit: I realized that sadly it's not as random as I thought it was. Locations like houses, trees etc are at different spots on the map and sometimes rotated, but they're still all the same and the same events occur. So if you play the game for the second or third time you can make different story related decisions (e.g. kill somebody you didn't kill last time), but besides that there's really not much variation, the radomness is very superficial, you pretty much know what's coming.It seems like the inner core of this game is the story, which forces the exploration & survival part to be kind of shallow and repetitive. That again makes exploring the story in different ways a bit dull, because there's all this predictable gameplay in between. Don't get me wrong, it's still a gripping game, but really only the first time you play it. I really whish they'd  either focused completely on the story or made a true random survival game. In my opinion, this fusion of both doesn't add up to some grate combination, it only subtracts and there's a lot of wasted potential."
